title: ld: file too small (length=0) *.rcgu.o

labels.name: S-needs-info
labels.description: Status: Needs more info, such as a reproduction or more background for a feature request.

body:
I got this error: ```text ld: file too small (length=0) file '~/mycrate/target/debug/deps/mycrate.1xfmugop1oyq9xx7.rcgu.o' for architecture x86_64 clang: error: linker command failed with exit code 1 (use -v to see invocation) ``` It repeated over mutliple runs of `cargo`, even after deleting the empty `mycrate.1xfmugop1oyq9xx7.rcgu.o` file, but went away as soon as I ran `cargo clean`. I don't know what triggered it but if I were to guess it would be having pressing ctrl+c before the previous invocation of `cargo run` had returned. ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.54.0-nightly (dbe459ded 2021-06-02) binary: rustc commit-hash: dbe459dedd33470f2cb28101157de316caaffa66 commit-date: 2021-06-02 host: x86_64-apple-darwin release: 1.54.0-nightly LLVM version: 12.0.1 ```
